<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[264,1325,284,470]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis box="[312,414,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Remarks</emphasis>
: The head pattern and strongly curved aedeagal shaft with an apical pair of processes distinguish this species from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[932,1080,324,349]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[932,1080,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Scaphoideus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1152,1202,324,350]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[300,448,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polymitus">
<emphasis box="[300,448,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. polymitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is missing; however, the label which bore the 
<typeStatus box="[1032,1082,364,390]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
reads “ 
<typeStatus box="[1178,1242,364,390]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Type</typeStatus>
, H.T.” “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Dist." authorityName="Dist." box="[277,611,404,430]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polymitus">
<emphasis box="[277,547,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Scaphoideus polymitus</emphasis>
Dist.
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[617,670,404,430]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
” “Myitta, Doherty” “Dist. Coll. 
<number box="[1052,1113,404,430]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="1911.0">1911</number>
­ 
<number box="[1122,1170,404,430]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="383.0">383</number>
”. The synonymy is based on the similarity of the colour pattern in the two species.
</paragraph>
